{"title": "Fables of Pilpay", "description": "These moralistic stories within stories date back to the Sanskrit text Panchatantra (200 BC \u2013 300 AD). They were first translated into Arabic by a Persian named Ruzbeh who named it Book of Kalilah and Dimna and then by Abdullah Ibn al-Muqaffa and later Joseph Harris in 1679 and then remodeled in 1818. Max Mueller noted that La Fontaine was indebted to the work and other scholars have noted that Jeanne-Marie LePrince de Beaumont and John Fletcher were both familiar with the fables. The Fables of Pilpay are a series of inter-woven fables, many of which deploy metaphors of anthropomorphized animals with human virtues and vices. (Summary by The introduction and Wikipedia)", "duration": 24395, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "14948", "name": "Abdullah Ibn al-Muqaffa\u02bf"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/pilpay_2106_librivox/fables_pilpay_2106.jpg", "copyright_year": "1872", "genres": ["Culture & Heritage Fiction", "Epistolary Fiction", "Myths", "Legends & Fairy Tales"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "LibriVox Volunteers"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Craig Campbell"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Lynne T"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "April Mendis"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "Preface", "readers": [15747], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/pilpay_2106_librivox/pilpay_01_al-muqaffa_64kb.mp3", "duration": 546}, {"section": 2, "title": "Introduction", "readers": [3374], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/pilpay_2106_librivox/pilpay_02_al-muqaffa_64kb.mp3", "duration": 564}, {"section": 3, "title": "The Story Of Dabschelim And Pilpay", "readers": [15806], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/pilpay_2106_librivox/pilpay_03_al-muqaffa_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1042}, {"section": 4, "title": "The Travelling Pidgeon", "readers": [3374], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/pilpay_2106_librivox/pilpay_04_al-muqaffa_64kb.mp3", "durati